Paul Orude, Bauchi The Bauchi State Chapter of All Progressives Congress (APC) has congratulated Adams Oshiomhole over his emergence as the national chairman of the party. In a statement signed by the chairman, Uba Ahmed Nana, the APC in the state felicitated with the new national chairman and other excos on their victory at its national convention held on June 23rd, 2018. “We equally felicitate‎ with all delegates and members of the party who attended the convention on our collective success. We sincerely appreciate them all and express our gratitude to Allah for returning us back to our various destinations in safety and journey mercies,”the party stated. The party also stated its heartfelt condolences to the families of members of the party including APC Chairman of Boi Ward in Bogoro local government area, Late Baba Phillip Iliya and other victims who were attacked and killed on the road at Riyom, Barkin Ladi and Jos South local government areas ‎on June 24th, 2018. “In the same vein, we sympathise with all those affected by the said attack in one way ‎or the other. We pray for Allah’s protection and quick recovery from all losses suffered as a result of the attacks. The party calls on people to remain calm and maintain peace in their respective domains as well as pray for stability, progress of the nation and success of the APC led government at the levels of the Federation. “We finally call on the Plateau state Government to identify, arrest and prosecute the killers along with their collaborators,” it urged. 